"principal veins lower body, external approach. this class includes one or more of 18 standard surgical interventions or procedures on component parts of the principal veins of the lower body with external approach.  these surgical interventions or procedures are listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 pcs under code 06.. . "
"principal veins lower body, external approach. this class includes one or more of 18 standard surgical interventions or procedures on component parts of the principal veins of the lower body with external approach.  these surgical interventions or procedures are listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 pcs under code 06.. revision of nonautologous tissue substitute in lower vein,  external approach. this classification denotes the group of activities that yields a surgical intervention or procedure to revision of nonautologous tissue substitute in lower vein,  external approach.this surgical intervention or procedure is listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 as code 06wyxkz. "

"principal veins lower extremities, percutaneous approach-part b. this class includes one or more of 18 standard surgical interventions or procedures on component parts of the principal veins of the lower extremities with percutaneous approach.  these surgical interventions or procedures are listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 pcs under code 06.. occlusion of left foot vein,  percutaneous approach. this classification denotes the group of activities that yields a surgical intervention or procedure to occlusion of left foot vein,  percutaneous approach.this surgical intervention or procedure is listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 as code 06lv3zz. "
"principal veins lower extremities, percutaneous approach-part b. this class includes one or more of 18 standard surgical interventions or procedures on component parts of the principal veins of the lower extremities with percutaneous approach.  these surgical interventions or procedures are listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 pcs under code 06.. occlusion of left foot vein with intraluminal device,  percutaneous approach. this classification denotes the group of activities that yields a surgical intervention or procedure to occlusion of left foot vein with intraluminal device,  percutaneous approach.this surgical intervention or procedure is listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 as code 06lv3dz. "principal veins abdomen, percutaneous endoscopic approach-part d. this class includes one or more of 18 standard surgical interventions or procedures on component parts of the principal veins of the abdomen with percutaneous endoscopic approach.  these surgical interventions or procedures are listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 pcs under code 06.. insertion of intraluminal device into left hypogastric vein,  percutaneous endoscopic approach. this classification denotes the group of activities that yields a surgical intervention or procedure to insertion of intraluminal device into left hypogastric vein,  percutaneous endoscopic approach.this surgical intervention or procedure is listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 as code 06hj4dz. "
